3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222895%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20medevac%20training%20exercise%20sees%20US%20soldiers%20moving%20a%20%26quot%3Bwounded%26quot%3B%20soldier%20to%20a%20helicopter.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67d0a948b8b41a9673fa5703%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221930%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESoldiers%20practice%20transporting%20a%20casualty%20to%20a%20UH-60%20Black%20Hawk%20helicopter.%3Cp%3ESgt.%20Tori%20Miller%2F124th%20Mobile%20Public%20Affairs%20Detachment%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20NDMS%20was%20originally%20created%20in%20the%20Cold%20War%20era%2C%20lawmakers%20realized%20that%20a%20war%20effort%20could%20not%20rely%20solely%20on%20the%20military's%20healthcare%20system%2C%20Friedrichs%20said.%20Rather%2C%20it%20would%20need%20to%20be%20augmented%20with%20the%20veteran's%20health%20administration%20and%20civilian%20partners%2C%20including%20hospitals%20and%20academic%20institutions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuch%20partnerships%20have%20fallen%20to%20the%20wayside%2C%20the%20panel%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20need%20to%20put%20our%20foot%20on%20the%20gas%2C%26quot%3B%20echoed%20retired%20Air%20Force%20Colonel%20Jeremy%20W.%20Cannon%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20surgery%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Pennsylvania%2C%20noting%20%26quot%3Bwe%20don't%20have%20five%20years%2C%2010%20years%2C%2020%20years.%20We%20need%20the%20solution%20really%20now.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNo%20one%20in%20the%20DoD%20truly%20owns%20combat%20casualty%20care%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added%2C%20making%20it%20harder%20for%20the%20military%20to%20even%20begin%20to%20better%20prepare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224b401864-282c-44bb-bc27-e7782bfde9b0%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20US%20military%20can't%20count%20solely%20on%20the%20systems%20that%20supported%20it%20in%20recent%20wars%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20military%20healthcare%20experts%20have%20expressed%20such%20concerns%20about%20combat%20casualty%20care%20may%20come%20as%20a%20surprise%20to%20some%20after%20two%20decades%20of%20war%20in%20the%20Middle%20East.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20height%20of%20combat%20in%20Iraq%20and%20Afghanistan%2C%20American%20air%20supremacy%20and%20regional%20support%20infrastructure%20meant%20troops%20could%20often%20be%20evacuated%20for%20higher-level%20medical%20care%20within%20the%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-warned-golden-hour-save-soldiers-threatened-russia-ukraine-lost-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egolden%20hour%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20window.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20logistics%20of%20warfare%2C%20including%20triage%20for%20the%20injured%2C%20is%20poised%20to%20be%20dizzyingly%20complex%20in%20the%20Pacific%2C%20especially%20as%20the%20US%20faces%20a%20severe%20shortage%20of%20ships.%20The%20US%20has%20just%20two%20hospital%20ships%20that%20are%20in%20need%20of%20replacement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20that's%20not%20even%20factoring%20in%20threats%20posed%20by%20enemy%20activity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdding%20to%20the%20complexity%20is%20that%20the%20military's%20health%20system%20remains%20siloed%20in%20their%20healthcare%20operations%20and%20training%2C%20without%20a%20truly%20meaningful%20%26quot%3Bjoint%26quot%3B%20approach%20to%20healthcare%2C%20said%20Friedrichs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJointness%20helps%20various%20parts%20of%20the%20military%20more%20easily%20work%20together%2C%20and%20creates%20standardization%20that%20can%20make%20fighting%20wars%20and%20taking%20care%20of%20the%20wounded%20easier%20and%20more%20effective.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20challenges%20don't%20stop%20there.%20Just%2010%25%20of%20military%20general%20surgeons%20are%20receiving%20the%20patient%20volume%20and%20variety%20needed%20to%20keep%20their%20medical%20skills%20sharp%20and%20prepared%20for%20combat%20injuries.%20In%20the%20absence%20of%20active%20warfare%20and%20without%20sufficient%20training%20opportunities