ly%20invited%20me%20to%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpros-cons-sleepovers-kids-risks-tips-safety-plan-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ebirthday%20sleepover%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20because%20our%20mothers%20were%20friends.%20We%20hadn't%20really%20spent%20time%20together%20since%20elementary%20school%2C%20and%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20go%2C%20but%20my%20mother%20said%20it%20would%20be%20rude%20not%20to%20attend.%20I%20dreaded%20that%20weekend%20for%20a%20month%3B%20it%20was%20just%20as%20awkward%20and%20uncomfortable%20as%20I%20imagined.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThat%20experience%20has%20stuck%20with%20me%20as%20my%20kids%20have%20started%20navigating%20social%20invitations.%20One%20of%20my%20sons%20was%20recently%20invited%20to%20a%20friend's%20house%2C%20but%20he%20wasn't%20feeling%20it.%20He%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-build-healthy-boundaries-2018-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Estruggled%20to%20say%20no%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20without%20upsetting%20his%20friend%2C%20so%20we%20discussed%20some%20options.%20In%20the%20end%2C%20I%20gave%20him%20an%20easy%20out%3A%20blame%20me.%20Tell%20his%20friend%20we%20had%20family%20plans.%20His%20look%20of%20relief%20said%20it%20all.%20And%2C%20the%20next%20time%20this%20friend%20invited%20him%20to%20do%20something%2C%20he%20was%20more%20than%20happy%20to%20go.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221c8c0aed-a6a3-43ad-b044-649dee2f1e31%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20teens%20know%20they%20can%20use%20me%20as%20an%20excuse%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20isn't%20the%20first%20time%20I've%20done%20this.%20My%20teenagers%20know%20that%20they%20can%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmom-wrote-viral-tardy-note-for-teenage-daughter-2016-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Euse%20me%20as%