0my%20kids%20to%20be%20kind%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20think%20most%20of%20us%20have%20used%20similar%20tactics%20to%20s%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-tell-when-teen-is-uncomfortable-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eidestep%20an%20uncomfortable%20situation%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20regardless%20of%20age.%20At%20the%20heart%20of%20this%20is%20the%20understanding%20that%20not%20every%20situation%20calls%20for%20a%20direct%2C%20unfiltered%20response.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20encourage%20kids%20to%20tell%20the%20truth%20but%20also%20teach%20them%20about%20kindness%20and%20tact.%20If%20my%20son%20doesn't%20want%20to%20go%20to%20a%20party%2C%20does%20he%20really%20need%20to%20tell%20his%20friend%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20want%20to%20hang%20out%20with%20you%20today%26quot%3B%3F%20Of%20course%20not.%20As%20adults%2C%20we%20wouldn't%20do%20that%20either.%20We'd%20soften%20the%20rejection%2C%20offer%20an%20alternative%2C%20or%2C%20yes%2C%20sometimes%20use%20a%20little%20white%20lie%20to%20make%20things%20easier.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThat's%20not%20to%20say%20I%20encourage%20dishonesty%20across%20the%20board.%20My%20kids%20know%20that%20honesty%20is%20non-negotiable%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20things%20like%20schoolwork%2C%20commitments%2C%20and%20personal%20responsibility.%20But%20social%20situations%20are%20often%20more%20nuanced.%20They%20require%20a%20level%20of%20diplomacy%20that%20teenagers%20are%20still%20figuring%20out.%20I'm%20all%20for%20it%20if%20giving%20them%20an%20easy%2C%20consequence-free%20excuse%20helps%20them%20navigate%20tricky%20situations%20with%20less%20stress.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229b26eea9-2eaf-4667-be80-7fdd6e7db1a9%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20want%20to%20be%20their%20safety%20net%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBeyond%20helping%20them%20avoid%20discomfort%2C%20this%20strategy%20also%20gives%20them%20an%20important%20safety%20net.%20They%20know%20that%20if%20they%20ever%20find%20themselves%20in%20a%20situation%20that%20feels%20wrong%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20it's%20peer%20pressure%20or%20just%20a%20bad%20vibe%20%E2%80%94%20they%20can%20use%20me%20as%20an%20out.%20No%20questions%20asked.%20%26quot%3BMy%20mom%20needs%20me%20home%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3BMy%20parents%20won't%20let%20me%26quot%3B%20are%20built-in%20escape%20routes%20that%20let%20them%20quickly%20remove%20themselves%20from%20a%20situation.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20I%20do%20think%20that%20learning%20to%20say%20no%20is%20an%20important%20life%20skill.%20But%20it's%20one%20that%20develops%20over%20time%20with%20experience%20and%20confidence.%20I%20try%20to%20keep%20the%20lines%20of%20communication%20open%20so%20that%20we%20can%20discuss%20these%20situations%20and%20their%20reasons%20for%20wanting%20to%20say%20no%2C%20which%20helps%20me%20better%20understand%20what%20they're%20dealing%20with.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20until%20my%20kids%20are%20comfortable%20navigating%20those%20situations%20on%20their%20own%2C%20I'll%20be%20here%2C%20offering%20them%20an%20easy%20out%20whenever%20they%20need%20it.%20And%20if%20that%20means%20taking%20the%20blame%20for%20a%20few%20declined%20invitations%3F%20I'm%20more%20than%20happy%20to%20play%20the%20bad%20guy.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmy-kids-use-me-as-excuse-say-no-to-friends-2025-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1741773962000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67cf2c5cb8b41a9673fa2fd8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmy-kids-use-me-as-excuse-say-no-to-friends-2025-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22I%20know%20getting%20out%20of%20social%20plans%20can%20be%20hard%20for%20kids%2C%20so%