%2F118927538.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia-indiatimes-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fmajority-of-the-world-has-polluted-air-report%2Famp_articleshow%2F118927538.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fmajority-of-the-world-has-polluted-air-report%2Famp_articleshow%2F118927538.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%224%20things%20on%20a%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20that%20matter%20way%20more%20than%20the%20college%20you%20attended%2C%20according%20to%20a%20tech%20and%20finance%20recruiter%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225472%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20close-up%20shot%20of%20a%20student's%20hand%20throwing%20a%20hat%20into%20the%20sky%20during%20a%20graduation%20celebration%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67d040ec69253ccddf98dc1e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223648%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECaitlin%20Wehniainen%2C%20the%20director%20of%20business%20development%20at%20On%20Cue%20Hire%2C%20said%20after%20five%20years%20of%20experience%20the%20type%20of%20degree%20a%20job%20candidate%20has%20becomes%20less%20relevant.%3Cp%3EOlga%20Dobrovolska%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ECaitlin%20Wehniainen%20has%20helped%20place%20top%20talent%20on%20high-visibility%20teams%20at%20Fortune%201000%20companies.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20said%20experience%2C%20accomplishments%2C%20ability%20to%20learn%2C%20and%20growth%20matter%20more%20than%20college%20names.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWehniainen%20looks%20for%20these%20attributes%20in%20various%20ways%20on%20a%20candidate's%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Caitlin%20Wehniainen%2C%20a%20staffing%20and%20recruitment%20expert%20and%20director%20of%20business%20development%20at%20On%20Cue%20Hire%2C%20based%20in%20Boca%20Raton%2C%20Florida.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20a%20recruiter%20placing%20candidates%20in%20corporate%20roles%20in%20IT%2C%20HR%2C%20finance%2C%20marketing%2C%20and%20other%20fields.%20I%20even%20started%20my%20own%20staffing%20and%20talent%20firm%2C%20On%20Cue%20Hire.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIn%20my%20years%20of%20recruiting%2C%20I've%20found%20that%20the%20name%20of%20the%20college%20or%20school%20someone%20attended%20is%20rarely%20a%20deciding%20factor%20when%20assessing%20their%20fit%20for%20a%20position.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20it's%20rare%20that%20I%20pay%20attention%20to%20a%20college%20or%20school%20name%20when%20evaluating%20an%20individual's%20credentials%20and%20ability%20to%20perform%20in%20any%20given%20role.%20Unless%20the%20position%20I'm%20hiring%20for%20is%20incredibly%20niche%2C%20most%20hiring%20leaders%20like%20me%20care%20far%20more%20about%20other%20assets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHands-on%20work%20experience%2C%20accomplishments%2C%20aptitude%20for%20learning%2C%20and%20growth%20mean%20more%20to%20me%20than%20the%20name%20of%20the%20college%20or%20university%20a%20job%20candidate%20attended.%20Here's%20how%20I%20look%20for%20those%20things.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f9d124ca-424a-4514-acab-f9ef84245fdc%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EDegree%20levels%20and%20types%20vary%20depending%20on%20the%20position%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I'm%20looking%20at%20marketing%20roles%20and%20sales%20positions%2C%20I%20tend%20to%20see%20many%20people%20with%20marketing%20and%20communications-related%20degrees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20IT%20roles%2C%20I%20generally%20see%20master's%20degrees%20in%20information%20systems%20and%20computer%20science.%20But%20really%2C%20I%20see%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20without%20degrees%20building%20phenomenal%20careers%20in%20skilled%20trades%20like%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20these%20applicants%20have%20developed%20their%20skill%20set%20from%20prior%20jobs%20or%20learning%20at%20home%2C%20where%20they%20download%20the%20software%20and%20teach%20themselves%2C%20tinkering%20with%20things%20as%20they%20go.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22740ac97a-17d1-4227-ab4d-ca069ca54042%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20more%20experience%20a%20candidate%20has%2C%20the%20less%20their%20degree%20matters%20to%20me%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20an%20individual%20has%205%20years%20of%20experience%2C%20the%20degree%20becomes%20less%20relevant.%20At%20that%20point%2C%20the%20company%20they%20worked%20for%20matters%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20hiring%2C%20I%20ask%20about%20the%20prior%20company.%20What%20did%20you%20do%20within%20that%20company%3F%20What%20value%20and%20contributions%20did%20you%20bring%3F%20Answers%20to%20these%20questions%20become%20much%20more%20important%20to%20me%20than%20what%20an%20applicant%20studied%20in%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224fffa040-e2f1-4967-b811-c7fd5a784323%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EPromotions%20within%20the%20same%20company%20are%20a%20good%20sign%20to%20recruiters%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%2C%20I%20look%20for%20visible%20promotions%20within%20the%20company%20or%20organization%20the%20candidate%20worked%20for.%20I%20want%20candidates%20who%20are%20fundamental%20contributors%20within%20their%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOften%2C%20I'll%20see%20someone%20who%20has%20been%20at%20the%20same%20company%20for%20three%20years%20and%20has%20job%20titles%20that%20go%20up%20the%20ladder.%20I%20see%20that%20and%20go%2C%20%26quot%3BOK%2C%26quot%3B%20this%20company%20is%20recognizing%20this%20person's%20talent%20and%20is%20giving%20them%20greater%20responsibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20this%20shows%20the%20candidate%20is%20highly%20capable%20and%20high%20performing%20in%20their%20job.%20They're%20probably%20a%20great%20professional%20because%20they're%20earning%20promotions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2234477944-cde4-462b-9b8a-2b3ff5999da8%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ECandidates%20should%20show%20recruiters%20they%20care%20about%20their%20craft%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20always%20great%20to%20see%20when%20someone%20is%20continuing%20their%20education%20in%20their%20field%20through%20furthering%20their%20degrees%20with%20a%20master's%2C%20Ph.D.%2C%20etc.%20This%20shows%20they're%20passionate%20about%20their%20career%20and%20care%20about%20their%20craft.%20They%20want%20to%20learn%20more%20about%20what%20they're%20doing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECertifications%20also%20add%20value%20to%20an%20applicant's%20candidacy%20for%20a%20role.%20I%20like%20to%20see%20applicants%20reach%20their%20long-term%20goals.%20For%20example%2C%20I%20value%20a%20candidate%20for%20a%20marketing%20role%20who%20has%20spent%20time%20earning%20an%20SEO%20certification.%20This%20means%20they%20spend%20personal%20time%20outside%20work%2C%20becoming%20a%20stronger%20professional%20in%20their%20field.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f88faeeb-25ea-4046-b854-191978f62679%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThere%20are%20only%20a%20few%20instances%20where%20school%20name%20matters%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20can%20be%20hundreds%20of%20applicants%20for%20just%20one%20role%20because%20LinkedIn%20and%20other%20job%20boards%20have%20one-click%20application%20systems.%20What%20makes%20a%20candidate%20stand%20out%20online%20is%20having%20a%20phenomenal%20LinkedIn%20with%20professional%20recommendations%20from%20previous%20hiring%20leaders%20or%20details%20about%20any%20other%20great%20project%20that%20they've%20accomplished.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20worked%20with%20Fortune%201000%20companies%2C%20placing%20top%20talent%20on%20high-visibility%20teams.%20Unless%20I'm%20searching%20for%20a%20high-level%20IT%20or%20software%20architecture%20role%20that%20might%20prioritize%20candidates%20from%20elite%20technical%20institutions%20like%20MIT%2C%20the%20school%20name%20doesn't%20typically%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EIf%20you're%20a%20talent%20recrui