20is%20raising%20questions%20about%20the%20future%20of%20such%20visas.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESee%20which%20tech%20companies%20file%20for%20the%20most%20H-1B%20visas%2C%20according%20to%20publicly%20available%20data.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ETech%20industry%20giants%20are%20hiring%20thousands%20of%20foreign%20workers%20through%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffinancial-companies-sponsor-h1b-visas-jpmorgan-goldman-sachs-blackrock-trump-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EH-1B%20visas%3C%2Fa%3E%20each%20year%2C%20even%20as%20the%20program%20faces%20renewed%20scrutiny%20under%20President%20Donald%20Trump's%20second%20term%20and%20growing%20skepticism%20from%20Silicon%20Valley%20leaders%20who%20once%20championed%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20H-1B%20program%20allows%20US%20companies%20to%20hire%20up%20to%2085%2C000%20foreign%20workers%20with%20specialized%20skills%20annually.%20Workers%20are%20chosen%20through%20an%20annual%20lottery%2C%20which%20kicked%20off%20last%20week%20and%20will%20run%20through%20March%2024.%20While%20Trump%20expressed%20support%20in%20December%2C%20calling%20it%20%26quot%3Ba%20great%20program%26quot%3B%20that%20he%20has%20%26quot%3Bused%20many%20times%2C%26quot%3B%20key%20figures%20in%20his%20political%20base%20have%20voiced%20opposition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThings%20escalated%20late%20last%20year%20when%20Trump%20appointed%20Sriram%20Krishnan%2C%20a%20first-generation%20Indian%20American%20who%20immigrated%20to%20the%20US%20from%20India%20in%202007%2C%20to%20serve%20as%20a%20senior%20White%20House%20advisor%20for%20AI.%20The%20appointment%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.google.com%2Fdocument%2Fd%2F1qVLx3axGaN1Y8JO_mfRG31BdAFaStzqNPiO_8s8sQGk%2Fedit%3Ftab%3Dt.0%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edrew%20backlash%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20some%20MAGA%20supporters%2C%20including%20former%20Trump%20aide%20Steve%20Bannon%2C%20who%20called%20the%20program%20%26quot%3Ba%20total%20and%20complete%20scam%20to%20destroy%20the%20American%20worker.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20late%20January%2C%20Republican%20Senators%20John%20Kennedy%20and%20Rick%20Scott%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kennedy.senate.gov%2Fpublic%2F2025%2F1%2Fkennedy-leads-resolution-to-reverse-biden-dhs-rule-automatically-extending-immigrant-work-permits%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eintroduced%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20joint%20resolution%20under%20the%20Congressional%20Review%20Act%20to%20reverse%20a%20Biden-era%20rule%20that%20extended%20the%20automatic%20renewal%20period%20for%20employment%20authorization%20documents%20from%20180%20days%20to%20540%20days.%20Kennedy%20said%20the%20extension%20%26quot%3Bhampers%20the%20Trump%20administration's%20efforts%20to%20enforce%20our%20immigration%20laws%2C%26quot%3B%20signaling%20there%20would%20be%20additional%20scrutiny%20of%20work%20permits%20for%20foreign%20nationals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20tech%20leaders%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.semafor.com%2Farticle%2F03%2F07%2F2025%2Ftech-gop-scuffle-ensues-over-h-1b-visa-program%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esoftened%20their%20stance%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Elon%20Musk%20and%20Marc%20Andreessen%2C%20once%20unequivocal%20supporters%2C%20have%20recently%20acknowledged%20the%20need%20for%20improvement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAndreessen%20said%20on%20Lex%20Fridman's%20podcast%20last%20month%20that%20the%20US%20has%20been%20conducting%20%26quot%3Ba%2060-year%20social%20engineering%20experiment%20to%20exclude%20native-born%20people%20from%20the%20educational%20slots%20and%20jobs%20that%20high-skill%20immigration%20has%20been%20funneling%20foreigners%20into.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%20has%20called%20for%20raising%20the%20minimum%20salary%20requirements%20for%20people%20on%20H-1B%20visas%20and%20adding%20a%20%26quot%3Byearly%20cost%26quot%3B%20to%20make%20it%20more%20expensive%20for%20companies%20to%20hire%20from%20overseas.%20%26quot%3BI've%20been%20very%20clear%20that%20the%20program%20is%20broken%20and%20needs%20major%20reform%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Felonmusk%2Fstatus%2F1873191959441084531%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eposted%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20X%3Cstrong%3E.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20program's%20future%20remains%20uncertain%2C%20any%20significant%20changes%20or%20restrictions%20to%20H-1B%20visas%20would%20profoundly%20impact%20America's%20largest%20technology%20companies%2C%20which%20have%20built%20their%20workforces%20around%20access%20to%20global%20talent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20used%20publicly%20available%20data%20from%20the%20Department%20of%20Labor%20and%20US%20Citizenship%20and%20Immigration%20Services%20to%20analyze%20which%20tech%20companies%20filed%20the%20most%20H-1B%20requests%20during%20the%202024%20government%20fiscal%20year.%20The%20data%20comes%20from%20applications%20submitted%20by%20businesses%20seeking%20to%20sponsor%20skilled%20workers'%20visas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20analysis%20shows%20that%20tech%20giants%20collectively%20file%20for%20thousands%20of%20these%20visas%20annually%2C%20using%20them%20to%20fill%20critical%20roles%20that%20they%20claim%20cannot%20be%20adequately%20staffed%20domestically.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20not%20every%20visa%20filing%20results%20in%20an%20actual%20hire%2C%20and%20occasionally%20multiple%20filings%20might%20be%20associated%20with%20a%20single%20position.%20Companies%20sometimes%20submit%20new%20applications%20to%20accommodate%20amendments%20or%20extend%20existing%20visas.%20Nevertheless%2C%20the%20data%20available%20to%20the%20public%20offers%20a%20reliable%20glimpse%20into%20the%20H-1B%20visa%20requirements%20of%20major%20corporations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20excluded%20IT%20consulting%20firms%20from%20this%20analysis%20to%20focus%20specifically%20on%20tech%20product%20companies%2C%20despite%20consulting%20giants%20like%20Infosys%20and%20Tata%20Consultancy%20Services%20traditionally%20being%20among%20the%20program's%20largest%20users.%3C