%3D%5C%222250%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20cardamom%20bun%20at%20La%20Cabra.%3Cp%3EMelia%20Russell%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20I%20licked%20my%20fingers%20clean%20of%20sugar%2C%20I%20scanned%20the%20cafe%20in%20search%20of%20employee%20badges%20or%20logo%20apparel%2C%20hoping%20for%20a%20glimpse%20of%20a%20startup%20executive%20in%20their%20natural%20habitat.%20In%20New%20York%2C%20unlike%20San%20Francisco%2C%20it%20seems%20that%20such%20overt%20displays%20of%20corporate%20allegiance%20are%20not%20as%20prevalent.%20Here%2C%20the%20tech%20elite%20and%20builders%20blend%20into%20the%20street%20milieu%2C%20swapping%20hoodies%20adorned%20with%20company%20logos%20for%20more%20voguish%20attire.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFeeling%20the%20caffeine%20buzz%20kick%20in%2C%20I%20left%20knowing%20that%20I'd%20return%20soon%20%E2%80%94%20if%20not%20for%20a%20meeting%2C%20then%20to%20try%20the%20pain%20suisse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fla-cabra-coffee-shop-review-openai-new-york-office-2025-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1741770001000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67d05ba7b8b41a9673fa47af%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fla-cabra-coffee-shop-review-openai-new-york-office-2025-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Puck%20Building%20is%20becoming%20the%20red-hot%20center%20of%20Manhattan's%20tech%20scene.%20That's%20led%20to%20crowding%20at%20the%20coffee%20shop%20across%20the%20street.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mrussell%40businessinsider.com%20(Melia%20Russell)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A78%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fla-cabra-coffee-shop-review-openai-new-york-office-2025-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Inside%20Larry%20Page's%20secret%20bet%20to%203D-print%20the%20future%20of%20air%20travel%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Larry%20Page%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67ced56e69253ccddf98bb59%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222071%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGoogle%20cofounder%20Larry%20Page.%3Cp%3EJustin%20Sullivan%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EGoogle%20cofounder%20Larry%20Page%20has%20a%20new%20startup%20exploring%20how%20AI%20can%20advance%20aviation%20manufacturing.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EPage%20appointed%20former%20Kittyhawk%20CTO%20Chris%20Anderson%20to%20run%20it.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20new%20company%20has%20consulted%20with%20researchers%20in%20the%20field%20of%203D%20printing.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flarry-page-kitty-hawk-flying-car-shutting-down-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWhen%20Google%20cofounder%20Larry%20Page's%20flying%20car%20startup%2C%20Kittyhawk%2C%20was%20winding%20down%20in%20late%202022%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20its%20chief%20technology%20officer%2C%20Chris%20Anderson%2C%20corralled%20a%20handful%20of%20employees%20and%20began%20working%20on%20something%20new.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnderson%20had%20for%20years%20been%20fascinated%20by%20the%20potential%20for%20additive%20manufacturing%20%E2%80%94%20also%20known%20as%203D%20printing%20%E2%80%94%20to%20transform%20the%20world.%20Page%2C%20for%20his%20part%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finside-kittyhawk-google-founder-billionaire-larry-page-flying-car-company-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehad%20pushed%20Kittyhawk%20engineers%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20explore%20the%20use%20of%203D%20printing%20to%20build%20parts%20of%20its%20flying%20vehicles%2C%20believing%20it%20could%20dramatically%20cut%20the%20cost%20of%20production.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20interests%20have%20collided%20in%20a%20new%20startup%20they%20formed%20called%20Dynatomics%2C%20which%20explores%20ways%20to%20use%20AI%20and%20additive%20manufacturing%20to%20build%20aircraft%2C%20according%20to%20business%20filings%20reviewed%20by%20Business%20Insider%20and%20multiple%20people%20familiar%20with%20the%20startup%2C%20who%20asked%20to%20remain%20anonymous%20because%20they%20were%20not%20permitted%20to%20speak%20publicly%20about%20the%20project.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDynatomics%20is%20funded%20by%20Page%20and%20run%20by%20Anderson%20out%20of%20Palo%20Alto%2C%20California%2C%20those%20people%20said.%20State%20corporation%20filings%20show%20the%20business%20was%20registered%20in%20California%20in%20June%202023%2C%20and%20a%20website%20domain%20name%20for%20Dynatomics%20was%20secured%20around%20the%20same%20time.%20The%20site%20is%20almost%20entirely%20empty%20except%20for%20a%20logo%20and%20a%20teaser%3A%20%26quot%3BWorking%20on%20something%20new.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20former%20Kittyhawk%20employees%20who%20work%20at%20Dynatomics%20are%20Stanford%20graduates%20who%20studied%20aerial%20robotics.%20On%20his%20personal%20website%2C%20Anderson%20describes%20working%20on%20a%20new%20stealth%20project%20%26quot%3Bat%20the%20intersection%20of%20AI%20and%20advanced%20manufacturing.%26quot%3B%20For%20a%20while%2C%20he%20had%20the%20name%20Dynatomics%20listed%20on%20his%20LinkedIn%20but%20later%20removed%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnderson%2C%20as%20well%20as%20representatives%20for%20Page%2C%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment%20from%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditive%20manufacturing%20involves%20building%20an%20object%20one%20layer%20of%20material%20at%20a%20time.%20The%20aviation%20industry%20already%20uses%20this%20process%20to%20reduce%20the%20cost%20and%20increase%20the%20speed%20of%20some%20components%2C%20and%20it%20becomes%20more%20difficult%20when%20producing%20larger%20parts%20or%20combining%20different%20materials.%20According%20to%20people%20familiar%20with%20the%20project%2C%20Page%20and%20Anderson%20are%20exploring%20how%20to%20use%20AI%20to%20improve%20the%20manufacturing%20process.%20The%20Information%20had%20previously%20reported%20on%20Page%20forming%20Dynatomics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20Kittyhawk%2C%20Page%20asked%20Anderson%20and%20then-CEO%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-sebastian-thrun-learned-to-be-visionary-from-larry-page-2019-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESebastian%20Thrun%20%3C%2Fa%3Eto%20have%20employees%20design%20flying%20vehicles%20using%203D-printed%20parts.%20Page%20believed%20it%20might%20be%20possible%20to%20reduce%20the%20cost%20of%20building%20flying%20cars%20by%20several%20magnitudes%20by%20using%20new%20forms%20of%20manufacturing%2C%20according%20to%20people%20who%20worked%20with%20him%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202023%2C%20Dynatomics%20turned%20to%20a%20research%20group%20at%20the%20Tallinn%20University%20of%20Technology%20in%20Estonia%2C%20which%20had%20just%20won%20a%20national%20research%20prize%20for%20its%20work%20in%20additive%20manufacturing%20of%20machines.%20Dynatomics%20paid%20the%20university%2060%2C000%20EUR%20for%20consultation%20services%20%26quot%3Brelated%20to%20additively%20manufactured%20electrical%20machines%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20filings%20in%20an%20online%20database%20that%20posts%20grant%20information%20and%20a%20person%20familiar%20with%20the%20partnership.%20Dynatomics'%20name%20was%20scrubbed%20from%20the%20grant%20after%20BI%20reached%20out%20to%20the%20university%20to%20inquire%20about%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%202023%20research%20paper%20by%20one%20Tallinn%20University%20researcher%20who%20consulted%20with%20Dynatomics%20described%20how%20using%20AI%20with%20additive%20manufacturing%20can%20%26quot%3Bmitigate%20print%20failure%2C%20reducing%20waste%2C%20cost%2C%20and%20production%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223c6cf5ed-f99d-4f81-9102-b49bb6726d1f%5C%22%3EPage%20pushes%20for%203D%20printing%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPage%20was%20compelled%20by%20the%20idea%20that%203D%20printing%20and%20cheap%20off-the-shelf%20components%20could%20offer%20a%20new%20path%20forward%20for%20electric%20vertical%20take-off%20and%20landing%20(eVTOL)%20aircraft.%20When%20he%20mandated%20Kittyhawk%20employees%20explore%20a%20series%20of%20projects%20using%203D%20printing%20technology%20in%202022%2C%20Anderson%20butted%20heads%20with%20some%20employees%20who%20felt%20Page%20was%20asking%20for%20things%20that%20defy%20the%20laws%20of%20physics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe's%20a%20lot%20more%20knowledgeable%20about%20aviation%20than%20I%20had%20any%20reason%20to%20believe%20before%20coming%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20Anderson%20told%20staff%20during%20a%202022%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flarry-page-flying-car-kittyhawk-leaked-audio-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emeeting%20with%20Kittyhawk%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20recording%20of%20which%20was%20obtained%20by%20BI.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20his%20thing.%26quot%3B%20To%20illustrate%20Page's%20obsession%20with%20aviation%2C%20Anderson%20told%20staff%20that%20Page's%20son%20had%20given%20his%20dad%20a%20T-shirt%20for%20Christmas%20that%20read%2C%20%26quot%3BI'm%20plane%20crazy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20frustration%20sometimes%20went%20both%20ways.%20Anderson%20made%20notes%20in%20an%20online%20calendar%20that%20was%20accessible%20to%20other%20staff.%20In%20one%20case%2C%20he%20wrote%20how%20he%20wished%20he%20could%20fire%20everyone%20at%20the%20company%20and%20start%20over%2C%20according%20to%20three%20former%20Kittyhawk%20employees%20who%20saw%20the%20note.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDynatomics%20may%20be%20his%20opportunity.%20When%20Anderson%20began%20forming%20his%20Dynatomics%20project%2C%20he%20plucked%20at%20least%20two%20people%20who%20had%20worked%20in%20a%20highly%20secretive%20skunkworks%20group%20within%20Kittyhawk%20known%20as%20%26quot%3BFeather%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20busied%20away%20on%20more%20ambitious%20and%20experimental%20ideas%20for%20flying%20vehicles%20%E2%80%94%20and%20had%20a%20rare%20direct%20line%20to%20Page.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2298dba879-1341-4d55-ac27-d3ced97ef7c0%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EPage%20and%20Anderson's%20close%20ties%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPage's%20bet%20on%20Dynatomics%20is%20a%20bet%20on%20Anderson.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20English-American%20writer%20and%20entrepreneur%2C%20Anderson's%20career%20has%20taken%20him%20from%20journalist%20to%20tech%20founder.%20He%20spent%20his%20early%20years%20studying%20physics%20and%20playing%20bass%20in%20a%20post-punk%20band%20named%20REM%20(culminating%20in%20a%20battle-of-the-bands%20showdown%20with%20the%20Michael%20Stipe-fronted%20namesake%20for%20the%20title%2C%20which%20Anderson's%20band%20lost).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20later%20worked%20as%20a%20journalist%20and%20editor%20at%20the%20Economist%20and%20Wired.%20In%202009%2C%20he%20co-founded%20the%20consumer%20drone%20company%203D%20Robotics%20and%20later%20sold%20it%20to%20Kittyhawk%2C%20the%20flying%20taxi%20startup%20run%20by%20driverless%20car%20luminary%20and%20ex-Googler%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finside-kittyhawk-google-founder-billionaire-larry-page-flying-car-company-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThrun%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20funded%20by%20Page.%20Anderson%20later%20became%20Kittyhawk's%20chief%20technology%20officer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Larry%20Page%20and%20Chris%20Anderson%20at%20the%20X%20Prize%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F678a3ea52fcded5e90739de0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222001%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELarry%20Page%20and%20Chris%20Anderson%20(right)%20at%20the%20Wired%20NextFest%20in%202007%3Cp%3EAmy%20Tierney%2FWireImage%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Anderson%20and%20Page%20knew%20each%20other%20long%20before%20Kittyhawk%2C%20former%20employees%20of%20the%20flying%20car%20company%20said%20the%20two%20men%20became%20closer%20after%20Anderson%20joined.%20Anderson%20would%20often%20journey%20over%20to%20Page's%20nearby%20home%20to%20discuss%20ideas%2C%20sometimes%20in%20Page's%20home%20garage%2C%20which%20was%20filled%20with%203D%20printers%20that%20he%20would%20tinker%20with%2C%20according%20to%20one%20of%20the%20people%20who%20heard%20it%20from%20Anderson.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe's%20a%20good%20engineer%2C%20which%20is%20what%20Larry%20likes%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20a%20person%20familiar%20with%20both%20men.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPage's%20decision%20to%20run%20Kittyhawk%20outside%20Alphabet%20%E2%80%94%20which%20houses%20a%20collection%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-layoff-moonshot-x-development-sergey-brin-larry-page-astro-2023-01%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emoonshot%20projects%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20allowed%20him%20to%20fund%20the%20project%20wholesale%20without%20answering%20to%20stockholders%2C%20who%20had%20often%20scrutinized%20Alphabet's%20spend%20on%20blue-sky%20ideas%20like%20driverless%20cars%20and%20internet%20balloons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20Kittyhawk%2C%20Page%20eventually%20wanted%20to%20design%20a%20flying%20car%20that%20could%20be%20manufactured%20for%20%2450%2C000%2C%20according%20to%20former%20employees%2C%20who%20said%20the%20company%20never%20got%20near%20that%20figure.%20Dynatomics%20could%20allow%20Anderson%20and%20Page%20to%20make%20good%20on%20what%20was%20once%20Kittyhawk's%20promise%20to%20%26quot%3BDemocratize%20electric%20aviation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20of%20the%20reasons%20the%20sky%20is%20empty%20is%20because%20it's%20quite%20expensive%20to%20get%20up%20there%2C%20and%20if%20airplanes%20were%20as%20cheap%20as%20cars%20and%20were%20made%20in%20the%20same%20volume%20of%20cars%2C%20it%20would%20change%20the%20nature%20of%20transportation%20and%20perhaps%20our%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20Anderson%20previously%20said%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.