Url%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Can%20Congress%20Ever%20Return%20In%20Gujarat%3F%20It%20Needs%20To%20Do%20These%203%20Things%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ERahul%20Gandhi%20recently%20threw%20an%20open%20challenge%20to%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%2C%20claiming%20that%20the%20Congress%20would%20defeat%20the%20BJP%20in%20the%202027%20assembly%20elections%20in%20the%20state.%20However%2C%20he%20highlighted%20several%20challenges%20the%20party%20faces%20in%20accomplishing%20his%20%E2%80%98Mission%20Gujarat'.%20The%20Leader%20of%20Opposition%20alleged%20that%20a%20section%20of%20partymen%20in%20the%20state%20has%20been%20in%20%26quot%3Bcollusion%26quot%3B%20with%20the%20BJP%20and%20that%20only%20after%20getting%20rid%20of%20such%20leaders%20the%20Congress%20will%20be%20able%20to%20do%20well%20in%20the%20state%2C%20where%20it%20has%20been%20out%20of%20power%20for%2030%20years%20now.%20Speaking%20to%20Congress%20workers%20in%20Gujarat%20on%20Saturday%2C%20Rahul%20said%20that%20the%20revival%20of%20the%20party%20in%20the%20state%20was%20not%20a%20%E2%80%9Ctwo-to-three-year%E2%80%9D%20but%20a%20%E2%80%9C50-year%20project%E2%80%9D%20adding%20that%20even%20if%20the%20party%20had%20to%20remove%20%E2%80%9C20-30%20people%E2%80%9D%2C%20it%20would%20do%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERahul's%20comments%20have%20sparked%20controversy.%20%E2%80%9CFrom%20alleging%20his%20party%2C%20people%2C%20constitutional%20institutions%2C%20and%20media%2C%20he%20has%20started%20blaming%20his%20own%20people.%20I'll%20suggest%20he%20do%20self-introspection%20instead%20of%20blaming%20others%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20BJP%20leader%20Sudhanshu%20Trivedi%2C%20highlighting%20the%20Congress's%20internal%20struggles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%202022%20Experience%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENo%20matter%20the%20rhetoric%2C%20defeating%20the%20BJP%20in%20Gujarat%20is%20no%20easy%20task.%20The%20Congress%20was%20routed%20here%20in%202022%2C%20winning%20just%2017%20seats%20(60%20less%20than%20in%202017)%20with%20a%2027%25%20vote%20share%20(a%20drop%20of%2015%20percentage%20points).%20In%20contrast%2C%20the%20Aam%20Aadmi%20Party%20(AAP)%2C%20which%20was%20just%20making%20its%20electoral%20debut%20in%20the%20state%2C%20ended%20up%20bagging%20an%20impressive%2013%25%20votes%E2%80%94at%20the%20expense%20of%20the%20Congress.%20This%20also%20resulted%20in%20a%20record%20mandate%20for%20the%20BJP%2C%20which%20got%20156%20seats%20with%20a%2053%25%20vote%20share.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%202022%20results%20were%20a%20big%20setback%20for%20the%20Congress%20considering%20its%20performance%20in%202017%2C%20when%20it%20had%20won%2077%20seats%20and%20scored%20a%2042%25%20vote%20share%2C%20pushing%20the%20BJP%20to%20less%20than%20a%20hundred%20seats%3B%20the%20latter%20got%20just%20seven%20more%20seats%20than%20a%20simple%20majority.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20three%20things%20the%20Congress%20must%20focus%20on%20to%20change%20its%20fate%20in%20Gujarat.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cb%3EHigh%20Command%20Needs%20To%20Introspect%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%2C%20to%20be%20fair%2C%20Rahul%20is%20not%20wrong%20in%20his%20analysis%20about%20Congress%20leaders%20in%20the%20state%20jeopardising%20the%20party's%20prospects.%20Each%20assembly%20term%2C%20it%20sees%20a%20clutch%20of%20MLAs%20switching%20to%20the%20BJP.%20The%20usual%20trajectory%20is%20that%20they%20resign%2C%20become%20BJP%20candidates%20in%20by-polls%2C%20and%20return%20to%20the%20assembly.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBetween%202017%20and%202022%2C%20some%20three%20dozen%20Congress%20MLAs%20and%20leaders%20joined%20the%20BJP.%20Even%20in%20the%20current%20assembly%2C%20the%20party's%20tally%20is%20down%20to%2013.%20Four%20MLAs%20resigned%2C%20joined%20the%20BJP%2C%20and%20then%20won%20the%20by-polls%20held%20recently.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20so%2C%20the%20Congress%20high%20command%20cannot%20escape%20full%20responsibility%20for%20the%20party's%20sorry%20state.%20Even%20after%20its%20stellar%20performance%20in%20the%202017%20elections%2C%20when%20it%20had%20benefited%20from%20the%20Patidar%20agitation%2C%20it%20ended%20up%20losing%20young%20firebrand%20leaders%20like%20Hardik%20Patel%20and%20Alpesh%20Thakor%20to%20the%20BJP.%20While%20Patel%20alleged%20that%20there%20was%20a%20lack%20of%20seriousness%20about%20all%20issues%20in%20the%20Congress's%20senior%20leadership%2C%20Thakor%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bweak%20leaders%26quot%3B%20were%20at%20the%20helm%20of%20affairs%20and%20that%20the%20OBC%20community%20wasn't%20getting%20the%20representation%20it%20deserved.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%20had%20consistently%20enjoyed%20a%20strong%20vote%20share%20of%2038%25%20to%2042%25%20between%20the%202002%20and%202017%20elections.%20However%2C%20internal%20sabotage%20and%20its%20inability%20to%20present%20an%20alternative%20vision%20gave%20way%20to%20the%20opposition%20AAP%20to%20claim%20some%20space%20in%20the%20state.%20According%20to%20exit%20polls%20after%20the%202022%20polls%2C%2013%25%20of%20Leuva%20Patels%2C%206%25%20of%20Kadva%20Patels%2C%206%25%20of%20OBCs%2C%2020%25%20of%20SCs%2C%205%25%20of%20STs%20and%2041%25%20of%20Muslims%20deserted%20the%20party%2C%20in%20comparison%20to%202017.%20Had%20AAP%20not%20been%20in%20the%20fray%2C%20the%20Congress%20theoretically%20might%20have%20won%2055%20seats%20in%20the%20last%20assembly%20polls.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EFind%20Serious%20Leaders%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHerein%20lies%20the%20second%20correction.%20Today%2C%20the%20Congress%20needs%2C%20more%20than%20anything%20else%2C%20to%20identify%20leaders%20who%20stand%20with%20the%20public%2C%20fight%20for%20them%20and%20respect%20them%2C%20and%20have%20the%20Congress%20in%20their%20heart.%20Those%20who%20do%20not%20fall%20into%20this%20category%20need%20to%20be%20weeded%20out.%20The%20control%20of%20the%20organisation%2C%20in%20the%20words%20of%20Rahul%2C%20%C2%A0should%20also%20be%20with%20such%20leaders.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20moment%20we%20do%20this%2C%20the%20people%20of%20Gujarat%20will%20want%20to%20storm%20into%20the%20party%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20has%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20order%20to%20make%20this%20possible%2C%20the%20old%20guard%20will%20need%20to%20make%20space%20for%20new%20leaders%20who%20can%20take%20on%20the%20BJP%20on%20the%20ground%2C%20raising%20local%20issues.%20The%20AAP's%20losses%20in%20Delhi%20and%20the%20dent%20in%20Kejriwal's%20clean%20image%20are%20opportunities%20that%20the%20Congress%20must%20bank%20on%20in%20order%20to%20regain%20the%20vote%20it%20had%20lost%20to%20the%20party%20in%20Gujarat.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWoo%20The%20Urban%20Voters%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20while%20the%20Congress%20has%20a%20strong%20base%20in%20Gujarat's%20rural%20areas%20(109%20seats)%2C%20the%20BJP%20has%20the%20upper%20hand%20in%20urban%20seats%20(74).%20But%2C%20with%20Gujarat's%20high%20urban%20population%2C%20the%20Congress%20cannot%20really%20afford%20to%20go%20down%20without%20a%20fight%20in%20such%20constituencies.%20In%202017%2C%20it%20was%20leading%2062-43%20in%20rural%20areas%20against%20the%20BJP%2C%20while%20in%20urban%20areas%2C%20it%20trailed%20at%2015-57.%20Of%20the%2036%20purely%20urban%20seats%20in%20three%20big%20cities%E2%80%94Ahmedabad%2C%20Vadodara%2C%20Gandhinagar%E2%80%94the%20Congress%20could%20win%20just%20five.%20To%20improve%20its%20tally%20in%20these%20areas%20in%202027%2C%20the%20Congress%20will%20have%20to%20win%20over%20the%20dominant%20middle%20class%20here%2C%20which%20favours%20a%20%E2%80%98business-friendly'%20BJP%20over%20an%20apparently%20%E2%80%98pro-Muslim'%20Congress.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithout%20these%20three%20steps%2C%20it%20would%20be%20difficult%20for%20the%20Congress%20to%20even%20dream%20of%20making%20a%20comeback%20in%20Gujarat%2C%20the%20BJP's%20strongest%20fortress.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Amitabh%20Tiw